#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md
msgid "Merging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:3
msgid ""
"In OCDS, merging involves combining individual "
"[releases](../../../getting_started/releases_and_records/) of data during"
" a contracting process into a "
"[record](../getting_started/releases_and_records/) which provides an "
"at-a-glance view of the current state and history of that process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:9
msgid ""
"A publisher provides a tender release on 1st January, with a planned "
"contract value of $1000."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:11
msgid ""
"On 31st January, the publisher provides an amended tender release "
"updating the planned contract value to $1500."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:13
msgid "After assessing bids, it is decided to award the contract in two lots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:15
msgid ""
"On 1st March, the publisher provides an award release, announcing Company"
" A have been awarded a contract for $750."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:17
msgid ""
"On 3rd March, the publisher provides an separate award release, "
"announcing that company B have been awarded a contract for $750"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:19
msgid ""
"These independent releases each provide real-time information about what "
"is happening in the contracting process. The record will combine them "
"together. Using the same schema and structure as the releases, the main "
"body of the record will contain a tender with contract value of $1500, "
"and details of both awards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/schema/merging.md:21
msgid ""
"If the record is complete with versioning information, then the "
"versioning section will reveal that the planned contract value changed "
"from $1000 to $1500 on 31st January."
msgstr ""

